
Overview of verb bake

The verb bake has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (6) bake -- (cook and make edible by putting in a hot oven; "bake the potatoes")
2. (1) bake -- (prepare with dry heat in an oven; "bake a cake")
3. (1) broil, bake -- (heat by a natural force; "The sun broils the valley in the summer")
4. bake, broil -- (be very hot, due to hot weather or exposure to the sun; "The town was broiling in the sun"; "the tourists were baking in the heat")
